section.section:
Each container of crab meat shall be marked by:
Embossing;
Imprinting;
Lithography; or
Subject to paragraph (2) of this subsection, any other method that the Department approves.

Each container of crab meat shall be marked with:
A description of the product in the container;
Subject to the requirements of paragraph (2) of this subsection, the name and address of the picking plant or the distributor;
If a chemical is added to the crab meat, a statement to that effect;
The license number of the crab meat plant preceded by the State abbreviation applicable to the picking plant;
The net weight of the contents of the container; and
Any other information that the Department requires.

A person may not possess more than 12 empty crab meat containers or container lids unless the person:
Is a manufacturer of containers or lids;
Is a licensed crab meat packer and the containers or lids are the same as used by the packer in the ordinary course of business;
Has removed the crab meat from the containers and lids for consumption on the premises; or
Is in possession of the containers or lids as provided for by the Department.
